    "body": "### Problem\n\nNeovim segfaults when I resize the outer terminal while the Codex TUI is running inside a terminal buffer managed by the `agent-term.nvim` plugin panel view.\n\nThis does not appear to be a generic terminal-buffer resize crash. A plain terminal split with Codex has not reproduced it, and another TUI, Gemini, works normally in the same plugin/panel setup. The failure currently looks like a non-standard interaction between the Codex TUI's terminal output/redraw behavior and the way `agent-term.nvim` hosts that terminal buffer in a persistent side panel.\n\nPlugin involved: https://github.com/alsi-lawr/agent-term.nvim\n\nThe crash is native rather than a Lua/plugin exception. The coredump consistently lands in Neovim's terminal rendering path, around libvterm input/glyph handling.\n\nBacktrace excerpt from `coredumpctl gdb nvim`:\n\n```text\nputglyph.lto_priv.0.cold\non_text.lto_priv.0\nvterm_input_write\nterminal_receive\non_channel_data\nread_event\nread_cb.lto_priv.0\nuv__read\nuv__stream_io\nuv__io_poll\nuv_run\ninbuf_poll\ninput_get\nstate_enter\nterminal_enter / normal_enter\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Install/use `agent-term.nvim`: https://github.com/alsi-lawr/agent-term.nvim\n2. Configure it to use the Codex preset/backend.\n3. Open the agent in panel mode.\n4. Leave focus in the hosted terminal TUI.\n5. Resize the outer terminal emulator window.\n\nI can reproduce the crash from the plugin panel with Codex. I have not reproduced it with Gemini in the same panel setup, and I have not reproduced it with a manually created terminal split running Codex.\n\nA manual terminal-buffer test that did not reproduce the crash:\n\n```vim\n:enew\n:call jobstart(['codex'], {'term': v:true})\n:botright vsplit\n:buffer #\n```\n\nResizing the outer terminal after that did not crash Neovim.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim should resize the terminal buffer/window without crashing, even if the hosted TUI emits unusual terminal control sequences during redraw.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n```text\nNVIM v0.12.2\nBuild type: Release\nLuaJIT 2.1.1774638290\n```\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNot tested. `vim` resolves to Neovim in this environment.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\n```text\nLinux nixos 6.18.24 #1-NixOS SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC Wed Apr 22 11:22:34 UTC 2026 x86_64 GNU/Linux\n```\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\n```text\nalacritty 0.17.0\n```\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\n```text\nxterm-256color\n```\n\n### Installation\n\nNix package / NixOS environment.\n",
